defaultLienert (2013) examined how constraints on legislators are essential in order to counter ‘deficit bias’. The specification of what legislators cannot do (eg increase total spending or reduce total taxes) 
defaultand can do 
defaultraises important issues
default of institutional design
default. Nevertheless, their scrutiny role is fundamental to the legitimacy of the budgetary process
