default There will be circumstances in which tax expenditures and coerced private expenditures are the most effective policy instrument. The concern here is that they will be over-used and used inappropriately, either because they are not monitored or are difficult to 
defaultmeasure
default.
default A specific issue is that the United Kingdom has aligned itself to private sector IFRS, with 
defaultinterpretations and 
defaultadaptations to meet specific public sector circumstances. Paradoxically, though the United Kingdom does not directly follow International Public Sector Accounting Standards (IPSASs), the research study commissioned by Eurostat 
defaultshowed that the
default United Kingdom
default has
default the highest rate of IPSAS compliance among the 
defaultthen EU27
default (Ernst &amp; Young, 2012)
default. This reflects the fact that IPSASs are themselves derived from IFRS. An open question is the extent to which the proposed EPSASs will derive from
default IPSAS or start from a different point. Unless the situation is carefully monitored, the United Kingdom could find itself non-compliant with EPSASs, or have to adopt accounting practices it believes inferior to its present practices, or engage in complicated reconciliations. 
